author: billbarker
msg: Fix for a couple of (mostly silly) edge-cases in testing auth.
If any security-contraint doesn't have a auth-constraint, then we pass.
Otherwise, if any security-constraint has an <auth-constraint />, then deny access to everyone.
Otherwise, much as before (e.g. allow to the first constraint that allows it).
